text: Margaret O'Brien (born January 15, 1937) is an American movie, stage and television actress who began acting as a child. She became famous through the movie Journey for Margaret (1942). She also played a French girl in the movie version of Jane Eyre in 1944. O'Brien was born in San Diego, California. ==Other websites== Category:Actors from San Diego Category:American movie actors Category:1937 births Category:Living people
